{"questionId":"12104","questionHtml":"<p>Hence find the area enclosed by the exponential function, the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>-axis, the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>-axis and the line <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 4.4\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4.4</mn>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Area&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\int\\limits_0^{4.4} {1.83{e^{0.986x}}dx = 140} \">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <munderover>\n    <mo>∫</mo>\n    <mn>0</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4.4</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </munderover>\n  <mrow>\n    <mn>1.83</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mi>e</mi>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>0.986</mn>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n        </mrow>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>d</mi>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>=</mo>\n    <mn>140</mn>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;units<sup>2</sup>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12104","referenceCode":"EXM.3.AHL.TZ0.7d.iv","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence find the area enclosed by the exponential function, the x -axis, the y -axis and the line x = 4.4 .","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"d.iv","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.8—Trapezoid rule","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.13—Non-linear regression","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.10—Scaling large numbers, log-log graphs"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}